Federer next played at the 2019 Cincinnati Masters and reached the third round where he lost in straight sets to Andrey Rublev. This was his quickest defeat in 16 years, taking just 62 minutes.[246] At the 2019 US Open, he was seeded third. He dropped the first set against both Sumit Nagal and Damir DÅ¾umhur in the first two rounds, but pulled out convincing straight sets wins over Dan Evans and David Goffin in the third and fourth. In the quarterfinals, he faced Grigor Dimitrov, who was ranked No. 78 going into the tournament. Despite taking a two sets to one lead, Federer ultimately lost the match in five sets.[247][248] At the 2019 Shanghai Masters, Federer defeated David Goffin in straight sets to reach the quarterfinal.[249] However, he lost the quarterfinal to Alexander Zverev in three sets.[250]
